# Changelog

All major changes to this project will be recorded in this file.


The format is based on [Keep a Changelog](https://keepachangelog.com/en/1.0.0/),
 and this project adheres to [Semantic Versioning](https://semver.org/spec/v2.0.0.html).


## [Unreleased]

## [0.3.3] = 2026-02-12
### Added
- **Year Filtering:** Added a dropdown on the home page to filter mileage entries by year.
- **Pagination:** Implemented pagination for the entries table (15 entries per page).
- **Smart Pagination UI:** Added logic to display a condensed range of page numbers (e.g., `1 ... 4 5 6 ... 10`) for better usability.
### Changed
- Updated the Home page title to dynamically display the selected year.
- Refactored `home` route in `app.py` to handle filtered and paginated SQL queries.
- Updated week number calculation in `utils.py` to use ISO calendar weeks. This ensures week numbers reset every year
 (e.g., Week 1 of 2025) instead of counting negatively from a fixed 2026 start date.
- Updated Stride CSV import logic to strictly enforce that the uploaded file's most recent week matches the selected
 entry week. If they do not match, an error is shown and the user is redirected to retry, preventing accidental zero-mile entries.
### Fixed
- Fixed an issue where re-uploading a CSV file after an error would fail to read the file content (added file pointer reset).
- Fixed CSV parsing for files containing a Byte Order Mark (BOM) by using `utf-8-sig` encoding.
- Prevented saving entries with 0 miles if the CSV parsing yields no valid data.

## [0.3.2] = 2026-02-05
### Changed
- Added a theme toggle button to the account page.
- Changes most CSS colors for backgrounds and borders to variables to use with the theme toggle.

## [0.3.1] = 2026-01-29
### Added
- Created a CHANGELOG file.
### Changed
- Updated the about page with more and better information.


## [0.3.0] - 2026-01-27
### Added
- User authentication: register (username, email, password) and login (username or email).
- Account page.
- Database records linked to the authenticated user.

## [0.2.3] - 2026-01-19
### Added
- Account page UI/content updates.
- Authentication links added to the navigation and footer.
- User management routes (logout and delete user).
- Export table data feature.

## [0.2.2] - 2026-01-16
### Added
- `requirements.txt` to document backend dependencies (e.g., Flask, python-dotenv).
- `SECRET_KEY` configuration and updates in `app.py` to use it.
- Flash messages for success, error, and warning.
- About page content and dedicated CSS.
### Changed
- Footer is now part of the page flow (no longer fixed on top of everything).
### Fixed
- Bug fix in `app.py`.
- Updated `.gitignore`.

## [0.2.1] - 2026-01-15
### Added
- Stride CSV upload on the Add page; parses mileage and calculates totals for the correct week.
### Changed
- Added comments throughout the codebase explaining what things do and why.

## [0.2.0] - 2026-01-14
### Added
- Edit page HTML templates.
- Responsive CSS (mobile + desktop) for the Edit and Add pages.
### Changed
- Tweaked CSS in the home files and base layout files.

## [0.1.1] - 2026-01-12
### Added
- Completed header and footer CSS for desktop and mobile base styles.
- Mobile hamburger menu (via script in `base.html`).

## [0.1.0] - 2026-01-09
### Changed
- Re-organized directories for layouts and images.
- Improved header interactions (hover movement) and added custom nav links (home, add, about, Google Sheets, Linktree, etc.).

## [0.0.2] - 2026-01-08
### Added
- Base template that renders different CSS files for different screen sizes.
- Started custom CSS work on the main page.

## [0.0.1] - 2026-01-07
### Added
- Initial form working and database displayed in a table.

## [0.0.0] - 2026-01-02
### Added
- Initial Flask app with routes and SQLite setup (initial push).

